title: deprecate the use of inline
body:
1. `inline::cfunction` would take a considerate amount of time to execute. The setup cycle is speeded up by compiling the interface functions at build time. The same mechanism is also used by `reticulate` to embed python.

2. As we move the compilations to build time, If JuliaCall is installed from a binary source, a compile tool (e.g., gcc) is not required to execute JuliaCall.

3. Support only Julia >0.6.
